cluding front-end and back-end developers, QA specialists, solutions architects, designers, and project managers.\n\nYou will collaborate closely with a team of back-end and front-end developers to help solve business problems for our clients.\n\nYour responsibilities will include developing back-end solutions using .NET, working on tasks such as integration layers, custom applications, and the setup of Azure infrastructure.\n\nIn conjunction with architects, designers and strategists, you will advise clients on making decisions about software and infrastructure based on their specific requirements. In Copenhagen we emphasize working in blended teams and learning from perspectives of other practices.\n\nYou will develop solutions that require integration across a variety of systems, such as CMS, CRM, PIM, DAM, ERP, and many more.\n\nWe build on the MACH-architecture, which means that:\n• Microservices – Our APIs consist of micro-service runtimes that communicate, and our integration layers are built on Azure Functions.\n• API-FIRST – Our solutions are API-driven, allowing front-end developers to deliver the best possible UX experience on top of the underlying APIs.\n• Cloud Native – We use the latest cloud services such as message queues, API gateways, and Function Apps in Azure.\n• Headless – Underlying CMSs are used in headless format and the presentation is not dictated by the CMS.\n\nAbout Novicell\n\nNovicell is a premier digital consulting firm dedicated to helping companies unlock their digital potential. By blending technical expertise with creative innovation, we deliver bespoke solutions tailored to our clients’ needs. Our diverse team of specialists collaborates with a singular focus: achieving exceptional results and pushing the boundaries of digital development.\n\nOur motto, “Kind & Diligent,” embodies our core values of integrity and collaboration. Rather than relying on traditional, lengthy employee handbooks and rules, we cultivate a culture of open dialogue and shared responsibility. We believe that a joyful work environment is crucial for employee satisfaction, motivation, creativity, and strong team relationships. At Novicell, we strive to make fun and joy an integral part of every workday. Hence, at Novicell, you will experience:\n• An informal organization with significant personal freedom.\n• A creative and inspiring environment where you can shape the company''s ongoing development.\n• A dedicated focus on personal and professional development.\n• A strong social culture with many activities and events.\n• The kindest and most diligent colleagues in the industry!\n\nRole and responsibilities\n\nAs a back-end .NET Developer at Novicell Copenhagen, you will:\n• Refine complex business requirements for our clients, breaking them down into manageable tasks that can be estimated and planned into sprints.\n• Advise clients on optimal solutions that perfectly align with their business needs, ensuring a balanced approach to scope, budget, and timeline.\n• Collaborate closely with cloud specialists to establish secure, future-proof hosting infrastructure with the necessary performance and scalability.\n• Work in tandem with front-end developers to discuss data and requirements, ensuring the creation of well-documented APIs.\n• Develop seamless integrations between various systems.\n• Partner with QA specialists to ensure a shared understanding and thorough testing of complex business logic.\n• Leverage CMS experience to build and configure CMS solutions for our clients, if applicable.\n\nAbout you\n\nTo succeed in this role, we expect that you\n• Have several years of experience building .NET solutions.\n• Have experience working with the latest .NET technologies.\n• Have experience in developing integrations and APIs.\n• Have experience working in a consultancy environment or engaging in dialogue with stakeholders. Ideally, you can understand business requirements and break them down into tasks.\n• Have experience with Azure Services, such as app services, functions, storage accounts, service bus, API gateways, etc.\n• Have experience with Azure DevOps, including build and release pipelines.\n• Have experience with CMS systems such as Umbraco, DynamicWeb, or similar.\n• Are self-driven, proactive, take responsibility, and follow through on tasks.\n• Can contribute knowledge to the team and across departments.\n\nHow to apply\n\nYou are welcome to submit your application and CV in English or Danish. This will have no impact on our assessment of your profile or skills.\n\nWe process applications continuously and will close the job opening once the right candidate has been found.\n\nRead more about Novicell here","job_is_remote":null,"job_posted_at":"8 days ago","job_posted_at_timestamp":"1741132800","job_posted_at_datetime_utc":"2025-03-05T00:00:00.000Z","job_location":"Copenhagen, Denmark","job_city":"København","job_state":null,"job_country":"DK","job_latitude":"55.676096799999996","job_longitude":"12.5683372","job_benefits":null,"job_google_link":"https://www.google.com/search?q=jobs&gl=dk&hl=da&udm=8#vhid=vt%3D20/docid%3DEi6w8ZvP2NUXaQmmAAAAAA%3D%3D&vssid=jobs-detail-viewer","job_salary":null,"job_min_salary":null,"job_max_salary":null,"job_salary_period":null,"job_onet_soc":"15113200","job_onet_job_zone":"4","employer_reviews":[{"publisher":"Glassdoor","employer_name":"Novicell Denmark","score":"3.9","num_stars":"4","review_count":"20","max_score":"5","reviews_link":"https://www.glassdoor.com/Reviews/Novicell-Reviews-E1403905.htm?utm_campaign=google_jobs_reviews&utm_source=google_jobs_reviews&utm_medium=organic"}],"job_highlights":{"Qualifications":null,"Benefits":null,"Responsibilities":null}}]}');
INSERT INTO public.job_details_result (id, job_id, json_response) VALUES (2, 'XrbVE8SbmTxFU-4VAAAAAA==', '{"status":"OK","request_id":"ce4a74f5-10bc-46d8-a862-ba62d000c899","parameters":{"job_id":"XrbVE8SbmTxFU-4VAAAAAA==","country":"dk"},"data":[{"job_id":"XrbVE8SbmTxFU-4VAAAAAA==","job_title":"Udvikler til teknisk test","employer_name":"TestHuset","employer_logo":"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRi_UQCMer4KGodDUOhq7cGpVTZhFQN7gnL1YpA&s=0","employer_website":"http://testhuset.dk/","job_publisher":"TestHuset Jobs - Trakstar","job_employment_type":"Full-time","job_apply_link":"https://testhuset.hire.trakstar.com/jobs/fk0q1f5/?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic","job_apply_is_direct":false,"apply_options":[{"publisher":"TestHuset Jobs - Trakstar","apply_link":"https://testhuset.hire.trakstar.com/jobs/fk0q1f5/?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic","is_direct":false},{"publisher":"Jobilize","apply_link":"https://www.jobilize.com/job/dk-ish-j-kommune-senior-udvikler-til-konsulenthus-work-supply-hiring?utm_campaign=google_jobs_apply&utm_source=google_jobs_apply&utm_medium=organic","is_direct":false}],"job_description":"Er du udvikler og har du interesse i test og kvalitetssikring?\n\nSå har vi måske stillingen til dig!\n\nVi søger tekniske testere som kan være med til at flytte vores kunder inden for blandt andet testautomatisering. Du kan enten være erfaren teknisk tester eller du kan være udvikler som har lyst til at prøve noget nyt. I begge tilfælde vil TestHuset kunne klæde dig på med de nyeste teknologier, personlig sparring og faglige inputs, således at du bliver en stjerne hos kunderne.\n\nTestHuset er den førende leverandør af ydelser og løsninger inden for test og kvalitetssikring i Danmark. Dette er ikke mindst på grund af vores dygtige og engagerede medarbejdere som brænder for softwaretest og som derfor gør en forskel hos vore kunder.\n\nDu kommer til at arbjede med følgende værktøjer:\n• Visual Studio\n• .Net framework (gerne C#)\n• SpecFlow/Nunit\n• Selenium WebDriver\n• SoapUI\n• TFS\n• Jenkins\n• Leapwork\n• Azure DevOps\n\nDu kommer bl.a. til at løse følgende opgaver:\n• Testanalyse og -design\n• Automatisering\n• Testeksekvering og fejlrapportering\n• Test af API\n\nVi forestiller os, at du:\n• Har en teknisk baggrund f.eks. teknisk tester eller udvikler, som vil noget mere, og som har lyst til at vise andre vejen til et bedre resultat\n• Du har måske en udviklerbaggrund eller en generel forståelse for en række teknologier/koncepter som f.eks. C#, VB, Python, XML, SQL, SOA, Linux, iOS, netværksprotokoller eller lignende\n• Evt. erfaring med Testautomatisering og Performanceværktøjer (Ranorex, QTP, Selenium, SoapUI, LoadRunner, JMeter, Silk...)\n• Brænder for at skabe værdi gennem kvalitet\n\nVi kan tilbyde dig det bedste!\n\nVi vil være de alllerbedste i branchen, og vores arbejdsmiljø bærer derfor et naturligt præg af en positiv faglig stolthed! Vi er i stand til at tilbyde dig en arbejdsplads, hvor fokus hele tiden er på at være innovative og sætte sit fremtidige præg på branchen, og hvor du kan være med til at udvikle nye forretningsområder og løsninger til vores kunder.\n\nMiljøet i TestHuset er unikt og uformelt samt i høj grad præget af dynamik og nytænkning. Dette gøres samtidig med en respekt for individet, da vi mener at en god balance mellem job og fritid er essentiel. Vi tilbyder en attraktiv lønpakke og et løbende fokus på personlig og faglig udvikling med tilknytning af både faglig mentor og personlig coach.\n\nDet er ikke kun os selv, der synes, at TestHuset er en god arbejdsplads. I 2015 blev TestHuset kåret til Danmarks 6. bedste it-arbejdsplads af Great Place to Work®.\n\nHvem er vi\n\nTestHuset leverer en lang række ydelser inden for Test, Continuous Integration og DevOps, og vi arbejder bredt med sikring af kvalitet gennem hele udviklingsprocessen hos vores kunder.TestHuset er en niche-virksomhed med specialister, der har fokus på at levere kvalitet til it-løsninger hos kunder, som er afhængige af it for at vækste deres forretning.\n\nHovedårsagen til vores succes er vores dygtige og engagerede medarbejdere, som brænder for at kvalitetssikre softwar på en effektiv og professionel måde, og som derved bidrager til at levere innovative og effektive løsninger til vores kunder.\n\nVi hjælper årligt mere end 100 klienter inden for mange forskellige brancher, herunder blandt andet pension, forsikring, bank, pharma, transport og den offentlige sektor men fælles for alle er, at deres it-løsninger skal være med til at vækste og sikre deres fremtidige forretning.\n\nVil du være med på vinderholdet?\n\nSend dit CV og en ansøgning til os via knappen \"Ansøg denne stilling\" herunder.\n\nHvis du har spørgsmål, er du velkommen til at kontakte Teamlead, Pia Vøgg, på telefon 6039 2887 eller e-mail pvo@testhuset.dk.\n\nDer er ingen ansøgningsfrist, men ansøgninger modtages løbende.","job_is_remote":null,"job_posted_at":null,"job_posted_at_timestamp":null,"job_posted_at_datetime_utc":null,"job_location":"Denmark","job_city":null,"job_state":null,"job_country":"DK","job_latitude":"56.26392","job_longitude":"9.501785","job_benefits":null,"job_google_link":"https://www.google.com/search?q=jobs&gl=dk&hl=da&udm=8#vhid=vt%3D20/docid%3DXrbVE8SbmTxFU-4VAAAAAA%3D%3D&vssid=jobs-detail-viewer","job_salary":null,"job_min_salary":null,"job_max_salary":null,"job_salary_period":null,"job_onet_soc":"15119900","job_onet_job_zone":"4","employer_reviews":null,"job_highlights":{"Qualifications":null,"Benefits":null,"Responsibilities":null}}]}');
